But though the date may be regarded as settled, other important points in the accounts we have remain still to be discussed Where was the monastery in which Enoch found the codex in question? What was the relation of this codex to the other known codices containing the historical books ol Tacitus? Did Enoch bring the original with him to Rome, or only a copy?
